{
  "time": "1800",
  "notes": "Client received from ED with right tibia-fibula fracture, cast in place. States he initially delayed seeking care for several hours because he was afraid of losing his job. Reports right leg pain as 10/10, describing it as a 'deep, burning pressure that never stops'. States the morphine given in the ED 2 hours ago 'didn't even touch it'. Client appears extremely anxious and restless. On assessment, the cast feels very tight. Distal skin at cast edges is pale, tense, and cool to the touch. Capillary refill in right great toe is 4 seconds. Client reports a 'pins and needles' sensation throughout the right foot and is unable to dorsiflex or plantar flex the ankle. Urine in Foley catheter bag is noted to be dark, tea-colored."
}

